WEBVTT

00:06.250 --> 00:07.458
Yo!

00:08.083 --> 00:09.125
Kevin!

00:09.208 --> 00:10.291
Oh!

00:10.375 --> 00:11.875
Uh-oh.
[chuckles]

00:11.959 --> 00:14.792
It is nice that we have
high ceilings in this house.

00:15.834 --> 00:18.083
We should totally put a trampoline
in the middle of our room.

00:18.166 --> 00:19.792
That would be awesome.

00:19.875 --> 00:22.667
We could somersault into bed
or backflip into the bathroom.

00:23.583 --> 00:25.834
Guys, do you really think
that's a good idea?

00:25.917 --> 00:28.792
Think. Think hard.

00:30.458 --> 00:31.458
No.

00:32.500 --> 00:34.083
Let's do this, come on.

00:34.458 --> 00:35.875
Hack it over here.

00:35.959 --> 00:37.917
Why, so you can kick it
into oblivion again?

00:38.000 --> 00:41.625
I can't help it if my leg muscles
are like crouching tigers.

00:41.709 --> 00:44.667
I had an off kick.
It happens to the best of us.

00:44.750 --> 00:46.500
And by "best," you mean "worst"?

00:46.583 --> 00:48.917
-[sighs]
-By "worst," you mean "best"?

00:49.000 --> 00:51.208
I bet you I can hack the sack
longer than you can.

00:51.291 --> 00:53.417
You're on... let's go... right now.

00:53.500 --> 00:56.625
House rules... two feet... no arms.

00:56.709 --> 00:58.917
Why are... we talking... so weird?

00:59.000 --> 01:02.959
-Good point... let's stop... right now.
-Are you ready now?

01:03.041 --> 01:04.917
No. I have to prepare.

01:05.250 --> 01:08.500
I need to hone in on
my razor-sharp reflexes.

01:08.583 --> 01:10.458
Good luck with that.

01:12.834 --> 01:14.542
One nanosecond off.

01:15.333 --> 01:16.500
I gotta work on that.

01:16.583 --> 01:17.959
[snorts]

01:19.208 --> 01:20.792
-[theme music playing]
-♪ <i>Yeah! ♪</i>

01:22.125 --> 01:23.875
<i>♪ Hey! ♪</i>

01:24.000 --> 01:26.000
<i>♪ I was sitting at home ♪</i>

01:26.083 --> 01:29.333
<i>♪ Watching TV all alone ♪</i>

01:29.417 --> 01:31.625
<i>♪ So tired of routines ♪</i>

01:31.709 --> 01:34.834
<i>♪ The day goes on and on ♪</i>

01:34.917 --> 01:36.917
<i>♪ So I pick up the phone ♪</i>

01:37.000 --> 01:40.375
<i>♪ Call everyone I know ♪</i>

01:40.458 --> 01:42.250
<i>♪ I say there's gonna be a party ♪</i>

01:42.333 --> 01:46.125
<i>♪ Hit the music, here we go, yeah ♪</i>

01:46.208 --> 01:49.667
<i>♪ You gotta live to party</i>
<i>Bust your move ♪</i>

01:49.750 --> 01:52.375
<i>♪ Everybody's in the groove ♪</i>

01:52.458 --> 01:55.041
<i>♪ Tell the DJ to play our song ♪</i>

01:55.125 --> 01:57.750
<i>♪ Are you ready to rock and roll? ♪</i>

01:57.834 --> 02:00.500
<i>♪ Gotta live to party</i>
<i>Bust your move ♪</i>

02:00.583 --> 02:03.375
<i>♪ Everybody's in the groove ♪</i>

02:03.458 --> 02:06.000
<i>♪ Live to ♪</i>

02:06.083 --> 02:08.125
<i>♪ Party! ♪</i>

02:13.041 --> 02:14.959
Guys, guess what.
Today's our anniversary.

02:15.041 --> 02:17.083
Aw, hug it out.
Bring it in.

02:17.208 --> 02:20.125
Feels good.
Ah, love it.

02:20.208 --> 02:22.792
You guys have no idea what anniversary
I'm talking about, do you?

02:22.875 --> 02:24.875
-Nope.
-Never claimed to.

02:25.542 --> 02:28.000
You guys, it's the anniversary
of when we first met Stella.

02:28.083 --> 02:29.458
Wow. Time flies.

02:29.542 --> 02:34.041
Feels like yesterday that wittle Stella
waddled into our wives.

02:36.333 --> 02:38.041
Sowwy.

02:38.125 --> 02:40.250
Any reason why you happen
to know the exact date

02:40.333 --> 02:42.417
-when we met Stella?
-Yeah, Joe.

02:42.500 --> 02:45.875
Any reason?
Thug-thug, thug-thug...

02:45.959 --> 02:47.792
Guys, I remember all important dates
that have to do

02:47.875 --> 02:50.000
-with our friends and family.
-Of course, you do, yeah.

02:50.125 --> 02:51.375
When's my birthday?

02:53.208 --> 02:55.083
Sometime this year?

02:55.166 --> 02:56.875
Lucky guess.

02:57.709 --> 02:59.875
Guys, it doesn't matter how I remembered.

02:59.959 --> 03:02.333
The important thing about remembering
is that I remembered.

03:02.417 --> 03:04.583
[Stella] Knock-knock.

03:04.667 --> 03:06.333
-Hey.
-Hi, Stella.

03:06.417 --> 03:08.375
Do you remember what today is?

03:08.458 --> 03:10.875
Oh, yeah, it's Be Kind To Chipmunks Day.

03:10.959 --> 03:12.500
I got your email, Kevin.

03:12.583 --> 03:14.875
Good, 'cause I got
an extra acorn for everybody.

03:16.709 --> 03:18.083
Oh, no, no, no, wait.

03:18.166 --> 03:21.709
Unless these t-shirts
answer your question.

03:21.792 --> 03:23.625
It's our 15-year "friend-a-versary."

03:23.709 --> 03:26.250
-Happy friend-a-versary.
-[both] Happy friend-a-versary!

03:26.333 --> 03:28.291
-I know.
-Fifteen years ago today,

03:28.375 --> 03:30.000
I spilled chocolate milk
all over my shirt,

03:30.083 --> 03:31.583
and you were the only person
that didn't laugh at me.

03:31.667 --> 03:33.125
Well, I mean, how could I laugh?

03:33.208 --> 03:35.458
Someone had to blot your
corduroy jumper with seltzer.

03:36.500 --> 03:38.458
Wow, think about it,
if you guys didn't meet,

03:38.542 --> 03:40.166
you guys wouldn't have become friends.

03:40.250 --> 03:42.083
And that way you wouldn't
become our stylist

03:42.166 --> 03:44.750
which means we would probably be walking
around the streets looking like this.

03:44.834 --> 03:47.083
<i>♪ Living life</i>
<i>Life in the fast lane ♪</i>

03:47.166 --> 03:48.583
<i>♪ Not that bad ♪</i>

03:48.667 --> 03:50.208
<i>♪ No, we can't complain ♪</i>

03:50.291 --> 03:51.583
<i>♪ Who's to say ♪</i>

03:51.667 --> 03:54.083
<i>♪ That we won't keep it real? ♪</i>

03:55.417 --> 03:57.959
<i>♪ Hold on tight, don't you get... ♪</i>

03:58.041 --> 03:59.750
[both shudder]

03:59.834 --> 04:01.709
It is a good thing I came along.

04:01.792 --> 04:04.625
Yeah, I mean, we need you like
the winter needs the spring.

04:04.709 --> 04:06.375
Or an ice cream cone needs sprinkles.

04:06.458 --> 04:10.875
Like a pirate needs a hook for a hand
and an eye-patch and a parrot.

04:11.000 --> 04:12.208
[mutters]

04:12.291 --> 04:15.166
Wow, you need
a lot of things to be a pirate.

04:25.959 --> 04:27.917
They're coming, I swear.

04:29.083 --> 04:32.542
Better late than never.
Finally, guys.

04:33.083 --> 04:34.291
So, guys, I was thinking.

04:34.375 --> 04:35.917
We should do something special for Stella,

04:36.000 --> 04:38.041
you know, for our "friend-a-versary,"
like, throw her a party.

04:38.125 --> 04:39.625
-Good idea.
-We need to figure out

04:39.709 --> 04:41.333
what kind of party a girl would like.

04:41.417 --> 04:43.333
-You know what we need for that?
-A girl.

04:44.250 --> 04:47.083
-Excuse me, miss!
-No, Joe, not just any girl.

04:47.166 --> 04:50.125
-We need Macy.
-You "Macy'd"?

04:50.208 --> 04:51.417
How did you do that?

04:51.500 --> 04:53.625
I wasn't following you
around trying to listen

04:53.709 --> 04:55.458
to your conversation,
if that's what you're suggesting.

04:55.542 --> 04:58.166
Macy, we need your help.
We want to throw a party for Stella.

04:58.250 --> 04:59.750
-Ooh!
-What kind of party

04:59.834 --> 05:01.250
would Stella really like?

05:01.333 --> 05:04.417
Stella loves surprises,
and I love surprises, too.

05:04.500 --> 05:07.250
I love ice cream and...
and party games and balloon animals.

05:07.333 --> 05:08.917
-Macy.
-Oh, right, Stella.

05:09.000 --> 05:11.333
Um... Stella loves karaoke.

05:11.417 --> 05:14.083
That's right. We can throw her
a surprise karaoke party.

05:14.166 --> 05:15.792
Can you come over later
and help us plan it?

05:15.875 --> 05:17.959
-Are you serious?
-We're serious.

05:18.041 --> 05:20.083
-Seriously.
-Hey, guys.

05:20.166 --> 05:23.917
-Shh, remember, big surprise.
-Oh, no, I'm not good at this.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.917
-Not good at what?
-[stammers]

05:27.000 --> 05:30.417
-Crunking.
-[hip-hop music plays]

05:30.500 --> 05:33.750
Hey! Let's, uh, crunk it up
over there, please.

05:33.834 --> 05:35.250
Oh, OK.

05:37.083 --> 05:38.875
[sighs]
He almost blew it.

05:39.959 --> 05:41.583
Almost blew what?

05:42.333 --> 05:45.417
-Uh...
-This trumpet. [chuckles]

05:45.500 --> 05:47.458
Right! 'Cause you're not allowed
to blow it in the hallway.

05:47.542 --> 05:50.583
-[chuckles]
-I'll just go put it in my locker.

05:50.667 --> 05:52.834
You know what?
That looks heavy. I'll go help you.

05:55.583 --> 05:57.959
-[rock music plays]
<i>-♪ Yeah</i> ♪

05:58.041 --> 05:59.709
<i>♪ Hey ♪</i>

06:01.125 --> 06:02.250
<i>♪ Hey! ♪</i>

06:04.000 --> 06:06.333
[sitar music playing]

06:10.667 --> 06:13.333
-What are you doing?
-Getting in touch with my inner Kevin.

06:13.417 --> 06:18.542
The Kevin that will prove
that your hacky sack is wacky sack.

06:18.625 --> 06:21.041
[laughs]
Well, can your inner Kevin do this?

06:27.250 --> 06:30.917
Your skills are great,
but can you do this.

06:31.000 --> 06:33.583
[inhales]

06:33.667 --> 06:36.542
-You didn't do anything.
-Not true.

06:36.625 --> 06:39.667
I beat you again... in here.

06:39.750 --> 06:44.417
It was awesome.
You're still crying... in here.

06:46.417 --> 06:49.667
Hey. Did I hear you guys
are having a hacky sack competition?

06:49.750 --> 06:51.667
You are correct, Father-son.

06:51.750 --> 06:55.250
Kevin's adopted this whole kung fu thing
to try and psych me out.

06:55.333 --> 06:56.917
Yeah, you can blame me for that.

06:57.000 --> 07:00.417
I let him watch too many kung fu movies
when he had the chicken-pox.

07:00.500 --> 07:01.500
I think it altered him.

07:01.583 --> 07:05.041
[dubbed] If I do not beat you,
my evil twin brother will,

07:05.125 --> 07:06.917
once he wakes up from his coma.

07:08.750 --> 07:10.667
Definitely the kung fu movies.

07:10.917 --> 07:13.000
You know, that or the high fever.

07:21.250 --> 07:22.458
[gasps]

07:22.542 --> 07:25.959
The Croonmaster 5000?
Stella's going to freak.

07:26.041 --> 07:28.000
She thought the 4000 was awesome.

07:28.083 --> 07:30.083
Yeah, but this one's even
a thousand times more awesome.

07:30.166 --> 07:33.291
But you've got to be a genius
to figure out how to turn this thing on.

07:33.375 --> 07:34.792
Let me see this.

07:35.083 --> 07:37.458
Mm-hmm.
Mm-hmm.

07:40.250 --> 07:42.667
[dance music playing]

07:45.041 --> 07:47.375
-[both] Wow.
-Genius in the house.

07:47.458 --> 07:49.417
[Stella]
Hello! Is anybody up there?

07:49.500 --> 07:50.834
[gasps]
Uh-oh! Stella's in the house!

07:50.917 --> 07:52.208
Hide the evidence!

07:54.083 --> 07:55.917
[beeping]

08:10.667 --> 08:12.458
Macy.

08:12.959 --> 08:16.750
What are you doing here...
on the floor... with Joe?

08:16.834 --> 08:20.792
I was...
helping him with his math homework.

08:20.875 --> 08:22.625
Uh... yeah.

08:23.417 --> 08:26.667
-I didn't know you were any good in math.
-Oh, she's very mathematical.

08:26.750 --> 08:32.208
-That's why they call her "Mathy Macy."
-No one has ever called her "Mathy Macy."

08:32.291 --> 08:34.208
And besides, I mean,
I thought I was the one

08:34.291 --> 08:35.583
that helped you with your math homework.

08:35.667 --> 08:37.709
Yeah, I just thought, you know,
I'd give you a break.

08:37.792 --> 08:39.417
I know what a handful I can be.

08:39.500 --> 08:42.667
-Yeah.
-Oh, well in that case,

08:42.750 --> 08:46.208
where are all the books,
calculators... the crying?

08:46.291 --> 08:48.417
Well, we're doing mental math.

08:48.500 --> 08:50.208
It's like jumping jacks for the brain.

08:50.291 --> 08:51.792
Yeah.
[chuckles]

08:52.125 --> 08:53.291
Oh.

08:54.125 --> 08:58.417
Well, I just brought these pants
to go with the friend-a-versary shirts.

08:58.500 --> 09:00.041
And now I'll go.

09:00.417 --> 09:03.291
Don't want to keep you two
from adding your figures together.

09:05.792 --> 09:07.458
-Bye.
-Later.

09:10.125 --> 09:12.542
So, what are you up to later?

09:12.625 --> 09:16.458
Huh? Oh, uh...
Sorry... Busy... Can't.

09:18.959 --> 09:20.792
But I didn't even
ask you anything yet.

09:20.875 --> 09:24.458
Um... Hey, Stella,
have you seen Mr. Newman today?

09:24.542 --> 09:26.000
He's wearing that terrible
sweater vest again...

09:26.083 --> 09:27.166
-[gasps]
-You know, with the cats' faces

09:27.250 --> 09:28.917
on the front,
and the cats' butts on the back.

09:29.000 --> 09:29.834
Yeah, he's right over there.

09:29.917 --> 09:31.625
[gasps]
No! Where's my phone?

09:31.834 --> 09:34.083
I have to get a picture of him
for my wall of shame.

09:34.959 --> 09:36.417
Wait, where?

09:39.500 --> 09:42.291
Macy? Macy?

09:43.166 --> 09:44.542
-Hey.
-Hey.

09:44.625 --> 09:46.583
We need to figure out
a way to keep Stella busy

09:46.667 --> 09:48.834
-before the surprise party.
-Right.

09:48.917 --> 09:50.500
We have to be sneaky.

09:50.583 --> 09:52.375
-Sneaky? About what?
-[both gasp]

09:52.458 --> 09:55.542
Uh, Sneaky is the name
of Macy's friend's cat.

09:55.625 --> 09:57.875
-She ran away from home.
-What?

09:57.959 --> 09:59.917
Oh! Right! [chuckles]

10:00.000 --> 10:04.709
Yeah, I better put up these flyers...
right after I make them.

10:07.375 --> 10:10.208
Hmm, so do you wanna maybe
do some homework later?

10:10.291 --> 10:14.667
Later... I can't.
I'm going to be doing homework.

10:15.417 --> 10:20.041
You can't do homework later
because you're too busy doing homework?

10:20.125 --> 10:23.709
-Yes.
-Oh. OK.

10:23.792 --> 10:27.834
Well, I won't be able to see you later
because I'll be too busy not seeing you.

10:27.917 --> 10:29.375
How do you like me now?

10:31.959 --> 10:33.500
Do you think she's onto us?

10:33.583 --> 10:36.583
-Doesn't suspect a thing.
-Good.

10:36.959 --> 10:38.750
So you're still coming over later, right?

10:38.834 --> 10:42.166
Oh, of course.
To do "homework."

10:54.875 --> 10:56.500
I know what's going on
between you and Joe.

10:56.583 --> 10:58.083
-You do?
-Yes, I do.

10:58.166 --> 10:59.709
All this sneaking off together.

10:59.792 --> 11:03.208
-We just wanted to surprise you.
-Wait, what? Surprise me?

11:03.291 --> 11:04.208
What are you talking about?

11:04.291 --> 11:05.583
What do you mean,
what am I talking about?

11:05.667 --> 11:07.542
-You like Joe.
-Of course, I like Joe.

11:07.625 --> 11:09.291
-I knew it!
-I know you knew it.

11:09.375 --> 11:11.208
-You knew I know it?
-How could I not know you know?

11:11.291 --> 11:12.875
-Macy!
-Stella!

11:12.959 --> 11:14.792
Wait, what are we talking about?

11:14.875 --> 11:16.875
-You like Joe!
-Of course, I like Joe!

11:16.959 --> 11:19.583
-I knew it!
-Oh! Whoa! Wait, wait.

11:19.625 --> 11:21.125
Stop the bus.

11:21.208 --> 11:25.083
There is nothing going on
between me and Joe.

11:25.166 --> 11:28.250
-[ringtone playing] <i>♪ Ooh ooh-ooh</i> ♪
-Oh.

11:28.542 --> 11:31.667
<i>♪ I'm feeling lovesick</i>
<i>But I don't mind ♪</i>

11:31.750 --> 11:33.959
<i>-♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh... ♪</i>
-Aren't you going to answer your phone?

11:34.041 --> 11:36.959
No. Because I love my new ring tone.

11:37.041 --> 11:40.125
-Doesn't it rock?
<i>-♪ Ooh ooh-ooh ♪</i>

11:40.208 --> 11:42.208
-It's Joe, isn't it?
<i>-♪ I'm feeling lovesick...</i> ♪

11:42.291 --> 11:44.417
Don't be silly.

11:44.583 --> 11:46.083
Let me see your phone.
Let me see your phone.

11:46.166 --> 11:48.000
-Let me see your phone--
-[phone shatters]

11:48.083 --> 11:49.583
[stomping]

11:51.875 --> 11:53.417
[groans]

11:54.500 --> 11:57.709
Oh! I think the battery just died.

12:04.709 --> 12:05.792
[grunts]

12:05.875 --> 12:07.959
[rock music playing]

12:16.875 --> 12:17.834
OK, spill it!

12:19.542 --> 12:21.166
You know, that was my last
glass of cranberry juice.

12:21.250 --> 12:23.625
You could've just said,
oh, I don't know, "Drink it."

12:24.417 --> 12:26.959
What is going on between Macy and Joe?

12:28.959 --> 12:32.000
-And by "Joe," you mean?
-You know who I'm talking about.

12:32.083 --> 12:34.250
Macy and Joe, they've been
spending a ton of time together.

12:34.333 --> 12:36.834
And they're acting
all secretive and weird.

12:36.917 --> 12:38.667
And by "weird," you mean?

12:38.750 --> 12:42.917
I mean weird!
Like mysterious, and annoying.

12:43.041 --> 12:46.208
Kind of like the two of you
are acting right now.

12:47.709 --> 12:50.333
[both]
Whatever do you mean, Stella Malone?

12:53.417 --> 12:58.375
Look, if Macy and Joe want to be together,
that's fine. I'm fine with that.

12:58.458 --> 13:01.583
I just don't like being the only one
who doesn't know about it.

13:03.041 --> 13:04.291
Here's your door.

13:05.667 --> 13:07.333
Joe! Joe.

13:07.625 --> 13:09.333
-Hey, want to hang Friday?
-Joe, look--

13:09.417 --> 13:11.542
-What?
-I thought we'd hang, chill,

13:11.625 --> 13:12.917
do some homework, you and me.

13:14.208 --> 13:16.667
Um... well...

13:17.458 --> 13:20.959
Yeah, I'm free.
Yeah, that sounds really great.

13:21.834 --> 13:23.792
Cool. Later.

13:26.583 --> 13:28.917
Why couldn't you have showed up
before she ripped my door off?

13:29.000 --> 13:30.875
You owe me a cranberry juice!

13:35.542 --> 13:37.208
-[pop music playing]
-OK, I'll get Stella,

13:37.291 --> 13:38.583
hang with her at school for an hour,

13:38.667 --> 13:40.917
then get back here for the big
friend-a-versary surprise party.

13:41.000 --> 13:43.917
OK. Let's synchronize our Jonas watches.

13:44.083 --> 13:46.625
I don't have a Jonas watch,

13:46.709 --> 13:49.792
but according to yours,
I'll be here ten past Nick.

13:49.875 --> 13:51.750
OK, but if you get here
a quarter to Kevin,

13:51.834 --> 13:53.667
-you've blown it.
-OK.

13:53.750 --> 13:54.875
OK.

14:05.166 --> 14:07.333
-Stella.
-Hey.

14:07.959 --> 14:10.083
What are you doing here?

14:10.166 --> 14:11.458
We were supposed to meet at school.

14:11.542 --> 14:14.333
Yeah, well, I thought it'd be
more fun if we hung out here

14:14.417 --> 14:16.917
so I brought popcorn
and rented a movie.

14:20.375 --> 14:24.208
-Aren't you going to let me in?
-Let's go get some ice cream.

14:24.291 --> 14:26.583
I know how you love ice cream.

14:27.417 --> 14:30.500
I never eat ice cream
unless a guy breaks up with me,

14:30.583 --> 14:33.750
which has never happened,
so I stand by my first statement.

14:35.291 --> 14:40.959
OK, tacos. Brokenhearted or otherwise,
everybody loves a good taco.

14:41.041 --> 14:42.583
<i>Vamanos.</i>

14:44.125 --> 14:46.709
-What's going on in here?
-Nothing.

14:48.417 --> 14:50.583
-Where is she?
-Where is who?

14:50.667 --> 14:53.583
-[groans] Macy!
-Macy?

14:53.667 --> 14:55.417
Why would Macy be here?

14:58.792 --> 15:01.375
-Let's dance.
-Huh? What?

15:01.917 --> 15:05.083
Joe, what are you doing?
[gasps]

15:05.792 --> 15:07.709
-I knew it.
-Hey, guys.

15:07.792 --> 15:09.000
[yelps]

15:09.458 --> 15:12.250
[stiffly]
Macy, what are you doing in my house?

15:12.709 --> 15:14.917
Uh, thanks for letting me
use your pole, Joe.

15:15.000 --> 15:16.250
Bye.

15:16.792 --> 15:18.166
Macy!

15:18.250 --> 15:19.709
Get back here, Macy Misa!

15:19.792 --> 15:22.000
Look! If you want to date Joe
behind my back,

15:22.083 --> 15:25.125
at least you could say it to my face.

15:29.166 --> 15:32.542
-These arms are made for sewing!
-Stella, wait!

15:35.917 --> 15:37.792
-[all] Surprise!
-Surprise?

15:37.875 --> 15:39.917
It's our 15-year friend-a-versary.

15:40.000 --> 15:43.208
Oh, no, no, no.
I can't believe it.

15:43.291 --> 15:47.417
So when you two were acting all dense
and all "Joe who?"

15:47.500 --> 15:50.417
-Just trying to keep a secret.
-Oh, you meant our Joe.

15:50.500 --> 15:52.542
Oh, OK.

15:53.166 --> 15:56.583
How about we crank up
the Croonmaster 5000?

15:56.667 --> 15:58.208
[gasps]
The 5000?

15:58.291 --> 16:00.959
That's supposed to be, like,
a thousand times more awesome

16:01.041 --> 16:04.125
-than the 4000.
-We know... thanks to Macy.

16:04.208 --> 16:06.750
She helped us plan this entire thing
with all your favorite stuff.

16:10.750 --> 16:14.208
Mace, um, I think I owe you
a huge apology.

16:14.291 --> 16:16.125
No, no, no. You don't need to
apologize for anything.

16:16.208 --> 16:18.375
I mean, I know you and Joe are...

16:18.625 --> 16:21.208
Well, you're not.
I mean, you are... so I would never.

16:21.291 --> 16:23.959
I mean, because you two...

16:24.041 --> 16:26.875
Do anything to get in the way of that.

16:26.959 --> 16:31.417
[laughs] Joe and I,
we're just really great friends.

16:31.500 --> 16:33.417
Yeah, great friends
who have feelings for each other,

16:33.500 --> 16:35.000
but don't want to jeopardize
their friendship

16:35.083 --> 16:36.625
so they just hope that someday

16:36.709 --> 16:39.583
they will be brave enough
to let their true feelings out.

16:41.458 --> 16:44.083
Or... whatever.

16:44.166 --> 16:45.709
Whatever, indeed.

16:46.500 --> 16:51.000
OK, OK, I admit...
I mean, sometimes I do wonder

16:51.083 --> 16:54.834
what it would be like
if Joe and I were brave enough.

16:59.667 --> 17:01.333
[PA feedback]

17:01.750 --> 17:04.834
[grunts] All right, everybody,
to get the karaoke started,

17:04.917 --> 17:07.125
I'm gonna sing
one of Stella's favorite songs.

17:07.208 --> 17:08.875
Happy friend-a-versary, Stella.

17:08.959 --> 17:11.917
-[cheering]
-[ballad playing]

17:29.792 --> 17:31.458
<i>♪ You ♪</i>

17:32.125 --> 17:34.875
<i>♪ You're like driving on a Sunday ♪</i>

17:34.959 --> 17:36.417
<i>♪ You ♪</i>

17:37.291 --> 17:39.875
<i>♪ You like takin' off on Monday ♪</i>

17:39.959 --> 17:41.458
<i>♪ You ♪</i>

17:41.542 --> 17:43.583
<i>♪ You're like a dream ♪</i>

17:43.667 --> 17:46.041
<i>♪ A dream come true ♪</i>

17:49.542 --> 17:51.500
<i>♪ In your eyes ♪</i>

17:52.375 --> 17:55.000
<i>♪ When I saw 'em for the first time ♪</i>

17:55.083 --> 17:56.125
<i>♪ Knew that I ♪</i>

17:57.417 --> 17:59.917
<i>♪ Was gonna love you for a long time ♪</i>

18:00.000 --> 18:01.709
<i>♪ With a love ♪</i>

18:01.792 --> 18:03.917
<i>♪ So real ♪</i>

18:04.667 --> 18:06.583
<i>♪ So right ♪</i>

18:09.917 --> 18:11.667
<i>♪ How ♪</i>

18:11.750 --> 18:12.792
[thunder rumbles]

18:12.875 --> 18:16.667
<i>♪ Did it play out like a movie, now? ♪</i>

18:17.750 --> 18:21.583
<i>♪ Every time its beat can move me</i>
<i>And I can't ♪</i>

18:22.041 --> 18:24.166
<i>♪ Get your smile ♪</i>

18:24.250 --> 18:26.792
<i>♪ Off my mind ♪</i>

18:30.417 --> 18:33.041
<i>♪ 'Cause you might think ♪</i>

18:33.125 --> 18:39.125
<i>♪ That I'm a fool for fallin' over you ♪</i>

18:39.792 --> 18:43.166
<i>♪ And tell me what can I do ♪</i>

18:43.375 --> 18:49.375
<i>♪ To prove to you</i>
<i>That it's not so hard to do? ♪</i>

18:50.333 --> 18:52.166
<i>♪ Give love a try ♪</i>

18:52.250 --> 18:55.125
<i>♪ One more time ♪</i>

18:55.208 --> 18:59.542
<i>♪ 'Cause you know that I'm on your side ♪</i>

19:00.458 --> 19:02.458
<i>♪ Give love a try ♪</i>

19:02.542 --> 19:05.041
<i>♪ One more time ♪</i>

19:07.667 --> 19:09.750
<i>♪ One more time ♪</i>

19:10.375 --> 19:13.166
[applauding and cheering]

19:15.792 --> 19:20.166
You know, I think it might be safer
if Joe and I are just friends.

19:21.750 --> 19:23.375
[people chattering]

19:25.542 --> 19:27.041
-Hey.
-Hi.

19:27.125 --> 19:29.750
Has anyone ever told you
that you have a really nice voice?

19:29.834 --> 19:32.041
A few people here and there.

19:32.291 --> 19:36.041
You know, you might even have
a future as a singer someday.

19:36.125 --> 19:39.917
[gasps]
Oh! All over my friend-a-versary shirt.

19:40.000 --> 19:43.083
Don't worry, nothing a little
seltzer won't get right out.

19:43.917 --> 19:45.250
Just like when we first met.

19:46.000 --> 19:48.792
Except you don't have pigtails,
and you don't punch me that much anymore.

19:48.875 --> 19:50.625
Do you need me to punch you
more often, Joe?

19:50.709 --> 19:51.542
Maybe a little bit.

19:51.625 --> 19:54.083
-[thuds]
-Thanks.

19:54.834 --> 19:57.750
-Ow.
-Well, that's what friends are for.

20:02.166 --> 20:04.875
I will be recording
this historic showdown.

20:04.959 --> 20:07.166
Don't worry,
if anything embarrassing happens,

20:07.250 --> 20:09.333
it will be going on the internet.

20:09.417 --> 20:10.417
All right, as with all
family competitions,

20:10.500 --> 20:13.625
we'll go in birth order.
So, Kevin, you're first.

20:14.250 --> 20:16.291
OK. Don't like the weight.

20:17.709 --> 20:19.000
Don't like the color.

20:20.417 --> 20:21.792
Don't like the circumference.

20:21.875 --> 20:23.750
Kev, would you just go already, please?

20:23.834 --> 20:24.959
Come on!

20:29.333 --> 20:31.000
[sighs]

20:34.417 --> 20:36.041
Here we go. You ready?

20:36.125 --> 20:36.959
OK.

20:41.083 --> 20:43.041
Oh, I'm out

20:43.875 --> 20:46.500
That's it? Three?

20:46.583 --> 20:48.959
-What? I'm exhausted.
-[scoffs]

20:49.041 --> 20:50.625
Oh, Dad.

20:51.417 --> 20:53.166
You want to lie down?

21:02.625 --> 21:04.750
"And then she says, 'I do.'"

21:04.834 --> 21:06.000
Aww.

21:13.792 --> 21:16.417
A hundred thirty-two to three.
Sorry, dude, I think I just won.

21:16.500 --> 21:19.375
-Or did you?
-Yes, I did. I just won.

21:19.458 --> 21:21.208
Or did I let you win?

21:21.291 --> 21:23.750
-No, I won.
-Or did you?

21:23.834 --> 21:25.041
[laughs]
This is classic.

21:25.125 --> 21:26.792
-Or is it?
-All right,

21:26.875 --> 21:28.667
I'm not even on this ride anymore.

21:28.750 --> 21:30.667
-Neither am I.
-Or are you?

21:31.583 --> 21:33.792
Looks like little one learned his lesson!

21:35.208 --> 21:36.667
Or did he?
